# Wrapper around `git config` for gorillanest
#  for the following reasons:
# 1) its easiest if gn-daemon has an argv[0] whitelist
#     for commands, however exposing the whole of `git`
#     is not a good idea
# 2) `git config` allows adding arbitrary fields,
#     which could lead to a theoritical situation
#     where an attacker hides data in plain sight
#     without ways to monitor or limit his uploads
